      <bioghist id="aspace_7ca5fe31e009aa9968c4cebf1cf75336">
         <head>Robert B. Fisk</head>
         <p>Robert Brown Fisk was born in Covington, Kentucky in 1852. He was an attorney and land developer in Gettysburg, Potter County, South Dakota from 1884 until his death after 1929.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_66f789248719aa9520de6aac4b3c10e6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Robert B. Fisk Papers consist of family correspondence and business papers created and accumulated by Robert B. Fisk during the course of his career as an attorney and land developer in Potter County, South Dakota. Correspondence broadly documents nineteenth- and early-twentieth-century South Dakota life, including the rapidly growing settler population, business and real estate transactions, politics and the transition to statehood, the conditions of workers and prisoners, and the effect of economic recessions on the local population. Additionally, letters from family members document life in contemporary Kentucky.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
